metadata.name: Gemrock #81
metadata.description:
In this work, strands of pearls and colorful stones are arranged together like particles of memory and light, creating overlapping layers of color and texture. The color combinations begin from a delicate opening, where tiny, radiant elements are placed one by one, forming dense rows of color and shape.
As this flow progresses, layers of complementary colors, like calm and internal waves, create smaller and more cohesive structures, as if we are witnessing an ocean of stones, pearls, and colorful reflections.

metadata.name: Drawing a canvas #2
metadata.description:
In this artwork, chaos finds its harmony. Colored stripes move with seemingly random energy, yet they come together to form a pixelated tapestry that is both chaotic and ordered, a testament to the beauty of unpredictability.

This collection is a heartfelt tribute to the loyal NFT collectors who have been unwavering supporters of my creative journey. Each piece in this collection is a token of gratitude for the community that has stood by me from the beginning.

It was born out of the launch of my inaugural NFT collection on the Ethereum blockchain via Foundation. 

"The beauty of reflection" NFT release on Foundation: https://foundation.app/collection/presale

SURFERS is a generative animated painting made from pixel array computations and modulo functions. It is an exploration of various dithering effects and the rhythmic qualities of pixel transformations.

metadata.name: Alienpillars #11
metadata.description:
"A rare type of bug that supposedly arrived on a cargo ship is destroying crops on planet Uctumi, in the binary system of Extronium. A wide variety of very resistant subspecies has mutated and it is necessary to study and identify all of them to obtain a gen-activated pesticide that will work on all of their variations. The pest department of the Uctumi central government is working hard on it, and they say that these strange critters are probably related to similar species that inhabited the planet Earth of the Solar system a long time ago and have spread over the galaxy."

My second piece using the p5.js raymarcher I wrote. The drawing is made of circles and lines based on the 3D data. I wanted to try something hairy as it's easy to draw lines aligned to the surface normal with this method. I also used a shader for the frame and the glitchy/sketch features.

Features 

body color: green-red-purple-yellow-blue-black
body tone: dark-light
spots color: orange-green-blue-yellow-white
hair tips: yes-no
hair #1: short-medium-long
hair #2: short-medium-long
head size: small-medium-large
head shape: long-spherical-wide
glitchy mode: 10% chance
sketch mode: 9% chance

metadata.name: Plottable Mountain Moons #163
metadata.description:
What makes this NFT have value? not only the digital is cool but it is the recipe to a plottable. Owning this NFT confers the right to request a physical plot (21cm square). @greweb will ask extra fees for this service => https://greweb.me/plots/nft

Full article: https://greweb.me/2021/12/plottable-mountain-moons

Plottable Mountain Moons generalize many explorations done this year. There are 13 inks, 9 different shape primitives with recursion, various intensity, and frequencies of noise,... and many rare cases to discover!

Digital and Physical art, hybrid and decoupled:
- The art is published via a digital NFT on Tezos blockchain ‚Äì its digital representation simulates fountain pen inks drawing on paper with animated effects.
- Token to the physical world: owning each NFT confer the power to request the related physical plot: https://greweb.me/plots/nft

@greweb ‚Äì 2021 ‚Äì tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM ‚Äì CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: Ersbla #253
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: SENTINELS #118
metadata.description:
The SENTINELS, with their cold, diamond forms, reign over an unsettling realm. Their presence exudes an aura of solemn guardianship, shrouded with unease. These are not friendly guides; they are silent arbiters of the unknown, both protectors and judges of the enigma that is their terrain. As you gaze into their world, let these haunting apparitions remind you of the vastness of the cosmos. 

The SENTINELS beckon you to explore the sinister beauty of the abyss, to question, and to wander through a digital realm where the eerie and the captivating coexist.

Paranoia is a necessary skill whenever a SENTINEL is involved.
 
SENTINELS is not only an exploration of the sublime-it also empowers collectors to generate physical artifacts from the void. With a keystroke, you choose your format:

Press ‚Äòs‚Äô or ‚Äò1‚Äô to save a compact version
‚Äò2‚Äô for a print-ready image
‚Äò3‚Äô for a high-resolution image
